This paper discusses a novel HTTP response header that improves the performance and privacy of DNS resolution. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of computer security (cs.CR), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), software engineering (cs.SE), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
